Well Architected Framework
	-) Stop Guessing -> use auto scaling
	-) You can test at production scale
	-) Automate
	-) Project Evolving Architectures
	-) Game days for improving with users

Design Principles:
	1. Scalability (H/V)
	2. Disposable Resources
	3. Automation: serverless, autoscaling, IaaS
	4. Loose Coupling (break it in components, microservices)
	5. Services, not Servers

Web Architecture Framework: 6 pillars and synergy among them
	1. Operational Excellence
	  -) Code everywhere
	  -) Automatic Documentation Annotate
	  -) Frequent, reversible changes
	  -) refine frequently
	  -) Anticipate failure and learn from all operational failures

	  -) Prepare (Cloud formation, Config)
	  -) Operate (Cloud formation, Config)
	  -) Evolve (Cloud formation, Config, CI/CD)

	2. Security
	  -) Strong identity foundation
	  -) Enable traceability
	  -) all layers
	  -) In transit and at rest
	  -) Keep people away from data
	  -) Security events (simulations)

	  -) Identity and Access Management (IAM)
	  -) Detective Controls
	  -) Infrastructure Protection
	  -) Data Protection
	  -) Incident Response

	3. Reliability
		Service Quotas = Service Limits (old name)

	4. Performance Efficiency

	5. Cost Optimization
	  -) Awareness
	  -) Use the cloud only

	6. Sustainability

AWS Well-Architected Tool
AWS Right Sizing -> Best size at lowest cost -> process

